e-height: 33px;color: #000000;padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top:=
 0;margin-bottom: 10px;">How to manage a pandemic<br>
&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3D"storyHeadline" dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"font-family: Helvetica=2CA=
rial=2Csans-serif;font-weight: bold;font-size: 30px;line-height: 33px;colo=
r: #000000;padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;margin-bottom: 1=
0px;"><strong id=3D"docs-internal-guid-3a99f037-7fff-636b-9beb-690d0a61402=
d"><img height=3D"370" src=3D"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Qs6o2npuZz=
811vvEt9v-LMhDEiYMmY_HEpY-xyaC21iFgsX4sx3WtBzyUciiQwRRpvJkz84W35Q6E_1lSbE-=
demwzT9T0qWYD5Qsq8BjFzhFYbB0ly5x6QUj7uEI5YGLJQdjxviH" style=3D"border: 0px=
 initial ; width: 600px; height: 370px; margin: 0px;" width=3D"600"></stro=
ng></p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 20px;">My first taste of coronavirus panic came early one morn=
ing in January. An email with the heading &lsquo;Important Information: Pl=
ease Read&rsquo; arrived from our son&rsquo;s elementary school. The paren=
ts of one of his teachers=2C who had recently returned from China=2C had b=
een infected&mdash;Singapore&rsquo;s cases 8 and 9=2C as it turned out&mda=
sh;and the teacher in question was being quarantined.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 20px;"><a href=3D"https://technologyreview.us11.list-manage.co=
m/track/click?u=3D47c1a9cec9749a8f8cbc83e78&id=3D0c47f8cc9e&e=3Ddb760db8f2" style=3D"color: #f90e1e;text-decoration: underline;">Singapore was amon=
g the first countries to suffer an outbreak</a>. In the months since=2C it=
 has been at once reassuring and unnerving to watch its journey from an ea=
rly hotspot to a kind of haven state=2C holding out doggedly against an in=
vader that has infiltrated so many others.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 20px;">Early commentary in the West focused on the failings of=
 China&rsquo;s autocratic system=2C which hid the severity of Wuhan&rsquo;=
s outbreak&mdash;at what we now know to be catastrophic cost. The more the=
 epidemic has spread=2C the more it has become clear that Western liberal=
 democracies have badly mishandled it too=2C ending up with severe outbrea=
ks that could&mdash;perhaps&mdash;have been avoided.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 0;">Yet it makes little sense to view the coronavirus as some=
 kind of perverse vitality test for liberal and authoritarian regimes. Ins=
tead we should learn from the countries that responded more effectively&md=
ash;namely=2C Asia&rsquo;s advanced technocratic democracies. In the West=
 the virus exposed creaking public services and political division. But Ho=
ng Kong=2C Japan=2C and South Korea have managed better=2C while Singapore=
 and Taiwan have kept the disease almost entirely under control=2C at leas=
t for now. <a href=3D"https://technologyreview.us11.list-manage.com/track/=
click?u=3D47c1a9cec9749a8f8cbc83e78&id=3D0f9b93c8b8&e=3Ddb760db8f2" style=
=3D"color: #f90e1e;text-decoration: underline;">Read the full story by Jam=
es Crabtree</a>.</p>
