acing=3D"0" width=3D"100%" class=3D"storyBodyTable">
                                <tr>
                                  <td valign=3D"top" class=3D"standardText=
">
                                    <div style=3D"font-family: Helvetica=
=2CArial=2Csans-serif;font-weight: normal;font-size: 17px;line-height: 24p=
x;color: #000000;"><p class=3D"storySubHeadline" style=3D"font-family: Hel=
vetica=2CArial=2Csans-serif;font-weight: bold;font-size: 23px;line-height:=
 26px;color: #000000;padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 5px;marg=
in-bottom: 5px;">The lonely reality of grieving online during social isola=
tion</p>

<p class=3D"storySubHeadline" style=3D"font-family: Helvetica=2CArial=2Csa=
ns-serif;font-weight: bold;font-size: 23px;line-height: 26px;color: #00000=
0;padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 5px;margin-bottom: 5px;"><m=
eta charset=3D"utf-8"></p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>A grim trend: </strong>The global coronavirus p=
andemic has forced people to think about death=2C while simultaneously upe=
nding the ways in which we are used to experiencing grief and loss. <a hre=
f=3D"https://technologyreview.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D47c1a9c=
ec9749a8f8cbc83e78&id=3D55dc6145f1&e=3Ddb760db8f2" style=3D"color: #f90e1=
e;text-decoration: underline;">The only option is to grieve online</a>.&nb=
sp;</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Not new: </strong>The coronavirus pandemic didn=
&rsquo;t create online mourning and grief. Facebook groups already connect=
 mothers grieving young children to each other=2C and social-media profile=
s often become memorials. Live-streaming=2C too=2C<a href=3D"https://techn=
ologyreview.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D47c1a9cec9749a8f8cbc83e78=
&id=3Dcd809a3bcd&e=3Ddb760db8f2" style=3D"color: #f90e1e;text-decoration:=
 underline;"> is already a part of how people grieve.</a> Well before coro=
navirus sent billions of people into lockdown=2C there were reasons not ev=
erybody could make it to a funeral.</p>

<p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"padding-top: 0;padding-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;mar=
gin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>An added pain:</strong> The covid-19 pandemic h=
as forced all those dealing with death to confront the possibility that th=
ey won&rsquo;t be able to access what mourners may need most: human touch=
=2C connection=2C and community support. <a href=3D"https://technologyrevi=
ew.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u=3D47c1a9cec9749a8f8cbc83e78&id=3D3ec=
56ffa30&e=3Ddb760db8f2" style=3D"color: #f90e1e;text-decoration: underlin=
e;">Read the full story</a>.</p>

